The paper focuses on the study and comparison of multipath routing protocols in Mobile Ad hoc Networks (MANETs), which is a subfield of computer networking and falls under the category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The paper also proposes an optimization to the existing routing protocols, which involves the use of a new search table and load distribution, indicating a possible application of data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the impact of network size, mobility, and network load on the protocol performance, which could fall under the category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI).
